00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:26,220
It makes me feel so old.

1073
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:38,340
"Age cannot wither her,

1074
00:45:38,540 --> 00:45:40,620
nor custom stale her infinite variety".

1075
00:45:42,460 --> 00:45:43,580
If I'd been Cleopatra,

1076
00:45:43,780 --> 00:45:45,780
I'd have put whoever said that to death.

1077
00:45:46,740 --> 00:45:48,140
[Laughing]

1078
00:45:48,660 --> 00:45:50,580
To tell you the truth,
I didn't enjoy it much.

1079
00:45:51,700 --> 00:45:53,660
Oh, you're so very, very young.

1080
00:45:56,140 --> 00:45:57,620
I'll grow out of it.

1081
00:45:57,820 --> 00:45:59,020
Hmm.

1082
00:45:59,460 --> 00:46:00,820
[Laughing]

1083
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:07,740
I may go abroad for a while.

1084
00:46:07,980 --> 00:46:08,580
Oh, where?

1085
00:46:08,700 --> 00:46:10,620
I don't know. Italy, France. abroad.

1086
00:46:18,660 --> 00:46:19,700
I say,

1087
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,580
about-- about
that under study,

1088
00:46:22,340 --> 00:46:24,020
is there any chance for Joan?

1089
00:46:24,980 --> 00:46:26,700
Tell her to write to me.

1090
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,500
Thanks. Good night.

1091
00:46:31,260 --> 00:46:32,940
Good night, darling.

1092
00:46:47,100 --> 00:46:48,660
An understudy, my foot.

1093
00:46:52,260 --> 00:46:53,580
[Exhales]

1094
00:47:15,540 --> 00:47:17,060
[Footsteps approaching]

1095
00:47:19,500 --> 00:47:21,180
Wait. Hold it.

1096
00:47:24,940 --> 00:47:26,340
[Door creaking]

1097
00:47:29,740 --> 00:47:31,460
It's from you know who.

1098
00:47:49,420 --> 00:47:51,100
I don't want to be disturbed.

1099
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:02,660
Good matinee?

1100
00:48:02,860 --> 00:48:03,660
All right,

1101
00:48:03,820 --> 00:48:05,420
but I'm not feeling very well.

1102
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:07,620
Draw up a chair. Sit down.

1103
00:48:15,020 --> 00:48:15,980
What's the matter?

1104
00:48:16,180 --> 00:48:18,300
Nothing. I haven't been sleeping.

1105
00:48:22,260 --> 00:48:24,060
I had a post card from Roger.

1106
00:48:24,700 --> 00:48:25,300
He's in Naples.

1107
00:48:25,460 --> 00:48:26,860
Says he's having a great time.

1108
00:48:27,060 --> 00:48:29,220
Yes, but you haven't come
here just to tell me that,

1109
00:48:30,180 --> 00:48:30,900
have you?

1110
00:48:31,100 --> 00:48:32,980
No, it's something else. I, uh...

1111
00:48:34,860 --> 00:48:36,940
I can't pay you back
the money that I owe you.

1112
00:48:38,020 --> 00:48:39,940
I know I said at the end of last month.

1113
00:48:40,140 --> 00:48:41,700
But I just don't have it.

1114
00:48:41,900 --> 00:48:43,460
I could pay it off.

1115
00:48:43,620 --> 00:48:45,660
I hate having to ask
for more time. But...

1116
00:48:45,980 --> 00:48:47,860
Don't be such a bloody
little idiot, Tom.

1117
00:48:49,540 --> 00:48:50,180
It's so humiliating, Julia.

1118
00:48:50,380 --> 00:48:52,260
Geez, when you said
you'd pay my tips for me,

1119
00:48:52,460 --> 00:48:54,220
how do you think that made me feel?

1120
00:48:54,420 --> 00:48:56,220
I said I'm sorry, I didn't mean it.

1121
00:48:56,660 --> 00:48:57,620
I was jealous of you

1122
00:48:57,820 --> 00:48:59,700
spending so much time with Roger.

1123
00:49:03,700 --> 00:49:04,980
I was jealous.

1124
00:49:05,180 --> 00:49:06,860
I was jealous of you going out

1125
00:49:07,100 --> 00:49:08,940
and having a good time without me.

1126
00:49:09,100 --> 00:49:10,220
Is that so horrible?

1127
00:49:10,420 --> 00:49:12,540
I should never have
accepted anything from you.

1128
00:49:15,060 --> 00:49:16,980
You're everything in the world to me.

1129
00:49:17,300 --> 00:49:17,780
You know that.

1130
00:49:17,780 --> 00:49:20,020
I love being with you.
I don't want to lose you.

1131
00:49:21,540 --> 00:49:23,580
I have few friends. Real friends.

1132
00:49:24,620 --> 00:49:26,220
And you're the only person in my life

1133
00:49:26,420 --> 00:49:28,460
with whom I can be entirely myself.

1134
00:49:29,580 --> 00:49:30,820
[Gasping]

1135
00:49:31,020 --> 00:49:32,500
Let's... let's go...

1136
00:49:35,020 --> 00:49:36,500
[Exhales]

1137
00:49:41,900 --> 00:49:43,820
Let's go on seeing each other. Please.

1138
00:49:47,100 --> 00:49:48,580
Oh, Julia.

1139
00:50:22,980 --> 00:50:24,420
[Giggling]

1140
00:50:26,700 --> 00:50:27,500
(Evie) Well, I've always said,

1141
00:50:27,700 --> 00:50:29,900
you're lucky you can cry
without your eyelids swelling.

1142
00:50:31,380 --> 00:50:32,460
Go to hell.

1143
00:50:32,660 --> 00:50:34,780
Well, you're looking a lot happier,

1144
00:50:35,500 --> 00:50:36,820
I'll say that for you.

1145
00:50:36,980 --> 00:50:37,980
I hope with good reason.

1146
00:50:38,180 --> 00:50:40,420
If you're thinking what
I think you're thinking,

1147
00:50:41,180 --> 00:50:42,220
then stop thinking.

1148
00:50:42,420 --> 00:50:44,460
All the same, Evie,
you know what I think?

1149
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:46,500
No, what do you think?

1150
00:50:46,940 --> 00:50:48,100
What mugs men are.

1151
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:50,340
Well, they can't keep
it in their trousers,

1152
00:50:50,700 --> 00:50:52,420
[Julia laughs] that's for sure.

1153
00:50:52,620 --> 00:50:54,180
You're a revolting hag.

1154
00:50:54,460 --> 00:50:55,860
[Julia giggling]

1155
00:50:56,180 --> 00:50:57,180
Yes, I am happier.

1156
00:50:57,340 --> 00:50:59,220
Everything will be all right now.

1157
00:50:59,900 --> 00:51:01,660
[Sighs] I can't help feeling...

1158
00:51:01,980 --> 00:51:03,340
I wish I didn't.

1159
00:51:03,540 --> 00:51:05,300
Deep down, I can't help feeling...

1160
00:51:05,860 --> 00:51:06,700
What?

1161
00:51:06,900 --> 00:51:08,740
A certain contempt for that boy.

1162
00:51:10,020 --> 00:51:11,380
He's so transparent.

1163
00:51:11,540 --> 00:51:13,740
# Life is just a bowl of cherries

1164
00:51:14,740 --> 00:51:16,740
# don't make it serious
life's too mysterious

1165
00:51:18,380 --> 00:51:20,460
# you work, you save, you worry so

1166
00:51:21,220 --> 00:51:23,780
# but you can't take your dough #

1167
00:51:24,300 --> 00:51:25,940
# when you go, go, go

1168
00:51:25,940 --> 00:51:27,420
# so keep repeating... #

1169
00:51:27,460 --> 00:51:30,420
Are you dancing with
me or with someone else?

1170
00:51:30,420 --> 00:51:31,060
I'm sorry,
I-- I-- I, uh,

1171
00:51:31,060 --> 00:51:33,740
I can't get over what her
royal highness just said to me.

1172
00:51:33,740 --> 00:51:34,460
What? What did she say?

1173
00:51:34,460 --> 00:51:37,300
She said I ought to come
and see them in the country.

1174
00:51:37,300 --> 00:51:38,140
And I was just thinking,

1175
00:51:38,140 --> 00:51:40,660
you think it's ok if
I asked her to dance?

1176
00:51:40,660 --> 00:51:42,660
Oh, you're such a dreadful snob, Tom.

1177
00:51:42,660 --> 00:51:46,060
I know. That's why England's
the best place for me.

1178
00:51:47,180 --> 00:51:48,420
I'm glad we quarreled.

1179
00:51:48,420 --> 00:51:51,660
We're closer now than we've ever been.

1180
00:51:52,940 --> 00:51:55,820
[Julia giggles]

1181
00:51:59,980 --> 00:52:02,860
[Avice moaning]

1182
00:52:03,580 --> 00:52:05,740
[Avice panting]

1183
00:52:05,740 --> 00:52:08,620
[Tom moaning]

1184
00:52:14,100 --> 00:52:16,980
[Both moaning]

1185
00:52:22,060 --> 00:52:24,900
[Tom grunts]

1186
00:52:25,420 --> 00:52:28,300
[Bell tolling]

1187
00:52:29,140 --> 00:52:30,260
Tom?

1188
00:52:30,260 --> 00:52:31,500
What?

1189
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:33,820
Can I ask you a favor?

1190
00:52:33,820 --> 00:52:35,860
Anything in the world.

1191
00:52:35,860 --> 00:52:38,940
You know Julia Lambert well, don't you?

1192
00:52:39,940 --> 00:52:42,700
No, not well, slightly.

1193
00:52:42,700 --> 00:52:43,620
Oh.

1194
00:52:43,620 --> 00:52:45,300
Have you been to bed with her?

1195
00:52:45,300 --> 00:52:45,980
Are you crazy?

1196
00:52:45,980 --> 00:52:48,020
She's old enough to be my mother.

1197
00:52:48,020 --> 00:52:49,820
What about her?

1198
00:52:49,820 --> 00:52:53,140
I heard on the grapevine
that she's doing a new play

1199
00:52:53,540 --> 00:52:55,780
called "Nowadays",

1200
00:52:55,780 --> 00:52:58,780
and there's a part for me in it.

1201
00:53:03,180 --> 00:53:05,380
So I wondered if you...

1202
00:53:05,380 --> 00:53:07,940
If I'd talk to her?

1203
00:53:07,940 --> 00:53:09,620
Yes. Please, Tom,

1204
00:53:09,620 --> 00:53:12,260
I'm doing a Sunday night
performance week after next.

1205
00:53:12,260 --> 00:53:15,500
Terrible play. Lovely
part. Good shop window.

1206
00:53:18,540 --> 00:53:20,460
If you could get
her to see me in it--

1207
00:53:20,460 --> 00:53:23,020
Is that all? Consider it done.

1208
00:53:23,020 --> 00:53:24,860
I can get Julia Lambert
to do anything I want.

1209
00:53:24,860 --> 00:53:28,260
She eats out of my
hand. The part's yours.

1210
00:53:29,500 --> 00:53:30,980
Don't be daft,

1211
00:53:30,980 --> 00:53:32,980
I'd be lucky to get an audition,

1212
00:53:32,980 --> 00:53:33,620
never mind the part.

1213
00:53:33,620 --> 00:53:37,060
You'll be in that play or
I'll never kiss you again.

1214
00:53:40,380 --> 00:53:40,860
Must say,

1215
00:53:40,860 --> 00:53:43,140
never thought you'd keep this up.

1216
00:53:43,140 --> 00:53:46,260
Nor did I. But tummies will be tummies.

1217
00:53:46,580 --> 00:53:48,620
Saw the preliminary
budget for "Nowadays".

1218
00:53:48,620 --> 00:53:51,300
hmm. looks promising.

1219
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:53,020
Must start auditioning. By the way,

1220
00:53:53,020 --> 00:53:56,100
have you ever heard of a
girl called Avice Crichton?

1221
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:57,820
The name rings a bell.

1222
00:53:57,820 --> 00:53:58,700
I'm told she's rather good.

1223
00:53:58,700 --> 00:54:02,060
I was wondering if she might play Sybil.

1224
00:54:02,060 --> 00:54:03,940
Guess how I heard about her.

1225
00:54:03,940 --> 00:54:06,820
How?

1226
00:54:08,020 --> 00:54:09,220
Through Tom.

1227
00:54:09,220 --> 00:54:12,100
[Pedal clanking]

1228
00:54:16,380 --> 00:54:18,420
He says she's clever.

1229
00:54:18,420 --> 00:54:20,740
She's playing in a Sunday night show.

1230
00:54:20,740 --> 00:54:21,220
Tom thinks

1231
00:54:21,220 --> 00:54:23,620
it might be worthwhile
to go and have a look-see.

1232
00:54:23,620 --> 00:54:25,220
- Well, why don't you?
- Can't.

1233
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:27,220
Going down to sandwich to play golf.

1234
00:54:27,220 --> 00:54:28,140
Staying the night.

1235
00:54:28,140 --> 00:54:30,620
Would it bore you awfully to go?

1236
00:54:30,620 --> 00:54:33,500
Tom'll take you.

1237
00:54:34,460 --> 00:54:37,340
I'll think about it.

1238
00:54:38,500 --> 00:54:40,700
Hmm, am I late or were you early?

1239
00:54:40,700 --> 00:54:42,180
The curtain goes up sharp at 8:00.

1240
00:54:42,180 --> 00:54:44,860
I hate getting to a
play after it's begun.

1241
00:54:44,860 --> 00:54:45,860
Remind me, uh,

1242
00:54:45,860 --> 00:54:48,820
what's the name of the actress
we're going to see tonight?

1243
00:54:48,820 --> 00:54:50,300
Avice Crichton. You met her.

1244
00:54:50,300 --> 00:54:51,540
She came to lunch at Taplow.

1245
00:54:51,540 --> 00:54:53,460
- We even fought over her.
- Did we?

1246
00:54:53,460 --> 00:54:54,460
- Mmm.
- I don't remember.

1247
00:54:54,460 --> 00:54:56,220
I can't wait to hear
what you think of her.

1248
00:54:56,220 --> 00:54:57,820
She's so nervous knowing
you're gonna be out front.

1249
00:54:57,820 --> 00:55:01,660
You know, these performances are like
rehearsals, but I said you'd understand.

1250
00:55:02,540 --> 00:55:03,780
BotToms up.

1251
00:55:03,780 --> 00:55:04,900
I had a letter from Roger.

1252
00:55:04,900 --> 00:55:07,940
He's having a fine old
time. He's in Rome now.

1253
00:55:07,940 --> 00:55:10,900
- Oh, yeah?
- She's awfully pretty.

1254
00:55:10,900 --> 00:55:12,740
Who are we talking about now?

1255
00:55:12,740 --> 00:55:14,580
Avice Crichton.

1256
00:55:14,580 --> 00:55:14,900
Oh.

1257
00:55:14,900 --> 00:55:17,220
Yeah, she's got a great
figure. And she's very fair.

1258
00:55:17,220 --> 00:55:19,220
What with platinum and peroxide,

1259
00:55:19,260 --> 00:55:22,340
there's no lack of blondes these days.

1260
00:55:22,580 --> 00:55:23,780
Hers is natural.

1261
00:55:23,780 --> 00:55:24,780
I wonder how you know that.

1262
00:55:24,780 --> 00:55:27,140
Keep the pace, Julia, don't rush it.

1263
00:55:27,140 --> 00:55:28,420
Nice and easy.

1264
00:55:28,420 --> 00:55:29,220
[Coughs]

1265
00:55:29,220 --> 00:55:30,620
God, this is undrinkable.

1266
00:55:30,620 --> 00:55:32,780
He'll have to make a fresh pot.

1267
00:55:32,780 --> 00:55:33,580
Julia, please don't.

1268
00:55:33,580 --> 00:55:34,660
[Bell tinkling] We'll be late.

1269
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:36,460
The first few minutes don't matter.

1270
00:55:36,460 --> 00:55:37,820
But I said we'd be there on the dot.

1271
00:55:37,820 --> 00:55:39,900
She's got a very good scene
right at the beginning.

1272
00:55:39,900 --> 00:55:41,900
I'm sorry, but I can't
go without my coffee.

1273
00:55:41,900 --> 00:55:43,540
Wilson, can you make a fresh pot?

1274
00:55:43,540 --> 00:55:46,780
[Sighing] This tastes of bitter aloes.

1275
00:55:46,780 --> 00:55:47,900
[Laughs]

1276
00:55:47,900 --> 00:55:50,780
Bravo!

1277
00:55:52,700 --> 00:55:54,700
[Audience applauding]

1278
00:55:54,700 --> 00:55:57,580
[Laughs]

1279
00:55:58,820 --> 00:56:01,700
[Piano playing]

1280
00:56:05,260 --> 00:56:08,900
(Avice) What time did the
doctor say he was coming?

1281
00:56:09,020 --> 00:56:11,140
Any moment now.

1282
00:56:11,140 --> 00:56:13,700
Which one's Avice?

1283
00:56:13,700 --> 00:56:15,500
The pretty one.

1284
00:56:15,500 --> 00:56:17,180
(Avice) Oh, Cynthia,

1285
00:56:17,180 --> 00:56:20,420
I do hope he will be able to help me.

1286
00:56:21,900 --> 00:56:24,460
(Prompter) "He's meant
to be a miracle worker."

1287
00:56:24,460 --> 00:56:27,740
He's meant to be a miracle worker.

1288
00:56:28,460 --> 00:56:29,300
[Gasps]

1289
00:56:29,300 --> 00:56:32,340
I do so want to see again, Cynthia.

1290
00:56:36,260 --> 00:56:39,140
[Sobbing]

1291
00:56:40,140 --> 00:56:42,620
[Piano continues playing]

1292
00:56:42,620 --> 00:56:44,260
[Exclaims]

1293
00:56:44,260 --> 00:56:46,060
[Sobbing]

1294
00:56:46,060 --> 00:56:48,940
[Knocking on door]

1295
00:56:52,300 --> 00:56:55,380
Miss Lambert, this is such an honor.

1296
00:56:55,860 --> 00:56:58,740
You were great.

1297
00:56:58,740 --> 00:57:00,540
I'm so glad to meet you again.

1298
00:57:00,540 --> 00:57:03,860
And it's awfully good
of you to come round.

1299
00:57:03,860 --> 00:57:06,100
I- I'm afraid it's not much of a play

1300
00:57:06,100 --> 00:57:09,340
but I took a fancy to the part.

1301
00:57:09,460 --> 00:57:11,340
Oh, my dear,

1302
00:57:11,340 --> 00:57:13,540
Please don't weep. You're nervous.

1303
00:57:13,540 --> 00:57:16,100
And nerves are the respect
we pay our audience.

1304
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:17,420
It was only the first few moments.

1305
00:57:17,420 --> 00:57:19,660
After that, you were
splendid, quite splendid.

1306
00:57:19,660 --> 00:57:22,380
- Thank you, miss Lambert.
- Of course.

1307
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:23,140
Thank you so much.

1308
00:57:23,140 --> 00:57:25,500
Good night, miss
Crichton, and thank you.

1309
00:57:25,500 --> 00:57:27,340
You're so good at being blind.

1310
00:57:27,340 --> 00:57:29,420
Oh, thank you.

1311
00:57:29,420 --> 00:57:30,420
Ask her.

1312
00:57:30,420 --> 00:57:32,620
Miss Lambert,

1313
00:57:32,620 --> 00:57:33,140
is it true

1314
00:57:33,140 --> 00:57:35,300
you're putting on a new play soon?

1315
00:57:35,300 --> 00:57:35,980
Yes.

1316
00:57:35,980 --> 00:57:38,340
If there's a part for me in it,

1317
00:57:38,340 --> 00:57:40,260
could I audition for you?

1318
00:57:40,260 --> 00:57:42,060
I'll tell Mr. Gosselyn about you.

1319
00:57:42,060 --> 00:57:44,260
If you were to put
in a good word for me,

1320
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:45,020
that would help so much.

1321
00:57:45,020 --> 00:57:48,540
I take my husband's advice
more often than he does mine.

1322
00:57:49,220 --> 00:57:52,180
Oh, and good night. Please, cheer up.

1323
00:57:52,420 --> 00:57:55,300
You should go a long way.

1324
00:57:59,740 --> 00:58:01,740
[Exclaims]

1325
00:58:01,740 --> 00:58:03,780
[Gasps]

1326
00:58:03,780 --> 00:58:06,660
[Screaming]

1327
00:58:08,780 --> 00:58:11,020
You didn't think much of her, did you?

1328
00:58:11,020 --> 00:58:14,340
On the contrary, I think
a great deal of her.

1329
00:58:14,340 --> 00:58:16,780
She's so energetic.

1330
00:58:16,780 --> 00:58:18,860
I don't feel like going to a restaurant.

1331
00:58:18,860 --> 00:58:20,420
Bolton, straight home, please.

1332
00:58:20,420 --> 00:58:23,300
Michael's away. We can talk.

1333
00:58:25,140 --> 00:58:25,580
Tell me,

1334
00:58:25,580 --> 00:58:27,900
have you been to bed
with Avice Crichton?

1335
00:58:27,900 --> 00:58:28,900
Of course not.

1336
00:58:28,900 --> 00:58:29,660
Why not? She's pretty.

1337
00:58:29,660 --> 00:58:33,100
