1351
00:59:04,540 --> 00:59:08,060
that I would never let sentiment
interfere with business.

1352
00:59:08,220 --> 00:59:09,780
What do you mean?

1353
00:59:09,780 --> 00:59:12,620
I think she's rather a find.

1354
00:59:13,460 --> 00:59:14,540
I'll tell Michael.

1355
00:59:14,540 --> 00:59:17,220
I'll insist she plays the part.

1356
00:59:17,220 --> 00:59:20,140
Oh, Julia, you're wonderful.

1357
00:59:21,900 --> 00:59:24,780
Hell, I'm so fond of you.

1358
00:59:26,660 --> 00:59:28,700
You...

1359
00:59:28,700 --> 00:59:31,580
I'm fond of you.

1360
00:59:37,900 --> 00:59:40,660
I've liked going to bed with you.

1361
00:59:40,660 --> 00:59:41,620
And it pleases me to think

1362
00:59:41,620 --> 00:59:44,220
that you liked going to bed with me.

1363
00:59:44,220 --> 00:59:46,260
[Laughs]

1364
00:59:46,260 --> 00:59:48,460
But let's face it.

1365
00:59:48,460 --> 00:59:51,220
I've never been in love with you

1366
00:59:51,220 --> 00:59:52,900
and you,

1367
00:59:52,900 --> 00:59:55,940
you've never been in love with me.

1368
00:59:56,820 --> 01:00:00,060
We both knew it couldn't last.

1369
01:00:00,700 --> 01:00:01,740
Hmm.

1370
01:00:01,740 --> 01:00:04,900
You're in love with
that girl, aren't you?

1371
01:00:05,500 --> 01:00:08,060
You might as well admit it.

1372
01:00:08,060 --> 01:00:10,940
Yes.

1373
01:00:17,940 --> 01:00:20,820
Go now. Please.

1374
01:00:25,100 --> 01:00:27,980
[Door closing]

1375
01:00:41,580 --> 01:00:43,060
For Christ's sake, Julia,

1376
01:00:43,060 --> 01:00:45,140
what do you think you're doing?

1377
01:00:45,140 --> 01:00:46,260
You disappoint me.

1378
01:00:46,260 --> 01:00:47,740
Oh, dear, oh, dear, you really do.

1379
01:00:47,740 --> 01:00:49,820
After all I've taught you?

1380
01:00:49,820 --> 01:00:51,020
You can't just stand there

1381
01:00:51,020 --> 01:00:52,660
like a spare prick at a wedding.

1382
01:00:52,660 --> 01:00:55,140
For Christ's sake,
Julia, assert yourself.

1383
01:00:55,140 --> 01:00:58,180
It's you that matters. You. Only you.

1384
01:00:59,340 --> 01:01:02,420
All's fair with love
and the theatre, ducky.

1385
01:01:03,340 --> 01:01:06,220
[Julia sobbing]

1386
01:01:08,220 --> 01:01:11,580
No one will ever know
how much I loved him.

1387
01:01:14,260 --> 01:01:17,140
he was my earth, my moon,

1388
01:01:18,260 --> 01:01:21,420
and all the stars in the firmament.

1389
01:01:25,020 --> 01:01:27,900
Farewell, my love.

1390
01:01:30,180 --> 01:01:33,060
[Audience applauding]

1391
01:01:38,340 --> 01:01:41,220
Oh, evening, Mr. Gosselyn.

1392
01:01:45,940 --> 01:01:48,380
I didn't expect you back tonight.

1393
01:01:48,380 --> 01:01:49,740
How was the golf?

1394
01:01:49,740 --> 01:01:50,940
Erratic.

1395
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:52,660
How was the girl?

1396
01:01:52,660 --> 01:01:53,940
Oh.

1397
01:01:53,940 --> 01:01:55,860
- Brilliant.
- Really?

1398
01:01:55,860 --> 01:01:57,740
Very talented.

1399
01:01:57,740 --> 01:01:58,780
Yes, but can she act?

1400
01:01:58,780 --> 01:02:00,420
Oh, she has to play Sybil.

1401
01:02:00,420 --> 01:02:02,660
She's very pretty. Audition her.

1402
01:02:02,660 --> 01:02:05,540
You'll see what I mean.

1403
01:02:08,060 --> 01:02:09,340
(Michael) I saw the play tonight.

1404
01:02:09,340 --> 01:02:12,180
(Julia) Hmm. We took 5 calls.

1405
01:02:12,180 --> 01:02:12,860
[Toothbrush clattering]

1406
01:02:12,860 --> 01:02:14,900
Julia, I've got something to say to you.

1407
01:02:14,940 --> 01:02:16,820
Don't fly into temper, just listen.

1408
01:02:16,820 --> 01:02:19,180
What is it?

1409
01:02:19,180 --> 01:02:22,260
Why did you give such
a lousy performance?

1410
01:02:22,260 --> 01:02:24,420
- A lousy performance?
- Mmm-hmm.

1411
01:02:24,420 --> 01:02:26,420
That just shows how little you know.

1412
01:02:26,420 --> 01:02:29,020
I've never acted better in my life.

1413
01:02:29,020 --> 01:02:30,620
Balls. You were awful.

1414
01:02:30,620 --> 01:02:32,260
They adored me tonight.

1415
01:02:32,260 --> 01:02:33,980
The public are jackasses.

1416
01:02:33,980 --> 01:02:34,820
You were barnstorming.

1417
01:02:34,820 --> 01:02:36,140
False from beginning to end.

1418
01:02:36,140 --> 01:02:38,340
How dare you speak to me like that,

1419
01:02:38,340 --> 01:02:39,140
you little shit?

1420
01:02:39,140 --> 01:02:42,260
Get out of my room! What do you know?

1421
01:02:42,500 --> 01:02:43,260
You can strike me,

1422
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:45,180
you can swear at me, you
can yell the roof off.

1423
01:02:45,180 --> 01:02:47,940
The fact remains that your
acting has gone all to hell.

1424
01:02:47,940 --> 01:02:49,700
And I'm not going to
start rehearsing nowadays

1425
01:02:49,700 --> 01:02:52,660
with you playing up like a drama
queen suffering from asthma.

1426
01:02:52,660 --> 01:02:54,540
Get someone else to play the part!

1427
01:02:54,540 --> 01:02:57,420
Don't be stupid, Julia!

1428
01:02:58,020 --> 01:03:00,100
I'm taking the play off on Saturday.

1429
01:03:00,100 --> 01:03:03,140
And then I want you to go abroad.

1430
01:03:03,220 --> 01:03:04,180
Have a break.

1431
01:03:04,180 --> 01:03:06,740
Go and see your mother in Jersey.

1432
01:03:06,740 --> 01:03:10,260
We'll start rehearsing
"Nowadays" when you...

1433
01:03:10,900 --> 01:03:13,780
when you get back.

1434
01:03:18,300 --> 01:03:21,140
Am I really that bad?

1435
01:03:21,380 --> 01:03:24,340
(Michael) Yes.

1436
01:03:27,980 --> 01:03:31,220
Don't let the world
outside cheapen your gifts.

1437
01:03:35,260 --> 01:03:37,780
And what Jimmie Langton used to say:

1438
01:03:37,780 --> 01:03:40,420
"Your only reality is the theatre."

1439
01:03:40,420 --> 01:03:42,660
I hate myself. I'm a slut.

1440
01:03:42,660 --> 01:03:45,980
I'm just a rotten bitch.
Rotten through and through.

1441
01:03:47,140 --> 01:03:50,140
Nevertheless, you're a great actress.

1442
01:03:52,140 --> 01:03:53,500
Not tonight.

1443
01:03:53,500 --> 01:03:56,380
No. Not tonight.

1444
01:03:56,780 --> 01:03:59,820
Oh, darling, I'm-- I'm
tired out. I...

1445
01:04:00,180 --> 01:04:02,060
So stupid of
me. I should--

1446
01:04:02,060 --> 01:04:04,940
[Shushing]

1447
01:04:05,980 --> 01:04:08,860
You're right. You're right.

1448
01:04:10,020 --> 01:04:10,820
[Sniffs]

1449
01:04:10,820 --> 01:04:13,780
The only thing is to go away.

1450
01:04:24,220 --> 01:04:27,100
Thank you.

1451
01:04:27,300 --> 01:04:30,180
[Seagulls cawing]

1452
01:04:40,460 --> 01:04:43,460
(Mrs. Lambert) It's so good to see you.

1453
01:05:18,940 --> 01:05:19,900
And no drafts,

1454
01:05:19,900 --> 01:05:22,060
that's very important, Julia, dear.

1455
01:05:22,060 --> 01:05:23,860
Aunt Carrie and I will be very careful

1456
01:05:23,860 --> 01:05:25,620
to see that you never sit in a draft.

1457
01:05:25,620 --> 01:05:28,980
And you must wear
socks and woolen vests.

1458
01:05:28,980 --> 01:05:31,060
I would sooner wear a shroud.

1459
01:05:31,060 --> 01:05:34,420
Oh, well, we will
discuss it in the morning.

1460
01:05:34,500 --> 01:05:37,380
[Seagulls cawing]

1461
01:05:48,300 --> 01:05:51,420
(Turnbull) Miss Avice Crichton.

1462
01:05:56,980 --> 01:05:58,260
Good afternoon.

1463
01:05:58,260 --> 01:05:59,340
Good afternoon.

1464
01:05:59,340 --> 01:06:00,820
I'm Michael Gosselyn.

1465
01:06:00,820 --> 01:06:03,180
Good afternoon, Mr. Gosselyn.

1466
01:06:03,180 --> 01:06:04,340
What are you going to do for us?

1467
01:06:04,340 --> 01:06:07,580
I thought I'd do something
from "Twelfth night".

1468
01:06:09,260 --> 01:06:10,540
Viola.

1469
01:06:10,540 --> 01:06:13,420
Ggood. In your own time.

1470
01:06:27,580 --> 01:06:30,540
"Make me a willow cabin at your gate

1471
01:06:32,020 --> 01:06:35,140
and call upon my soul within the house"

1472
01:06:35,740 --> 01:06:39,060
Now do it as if you've got a cold.

1473
01:06:41,540 --> 01:06:42,660
I beg your pardon?

1474
01:06:42,660 --> 01:06:44,180
Can you do it again,

1475
01:06:44,180 --> 01:06:45,020
but this time

1476
01:06:45,020 --> 01:06:48,020
as if you've got a bad cold in the nose.

1477
01:06:58,780 --> 01:07:01,980
[Nasalized] "Make me a
willow cabin at your gate

1478
01:07:02,780 --> 01:07:03,620
[Dolly snickering]

1479
01:07:03,620 --> 01:07:06,740
"and call upon my soul within the house

1480
01:07:08,180 --> 01:07:09,780
[Sniffs]

1481
01:07:09,780 --> 01:07:12,460
"write loyal cantons of contemned love

1482
01:07:12,460 --> 01:07:15,980
"and sing them loud
even in the dead of night

1483
01:07:18,620 --> 01:07:20,100
[Laughing]

1484
01:07:20,100 --> 01:07:21,020
Halloo
your name-- "

