1518
01:08:54,100 --> 01:08:56,940
- but of course you know that.
- What new girl?

1519
01:08:56,940 --> 01:08:58,540
The one who's to be in your next play.

1520
01:08:58,540 --> 01:09:01,540
Her name's Avice Crichton,
something like that.

1521
01:09:01,540 --> 01:09:04,540
Michael says she's to
be the new Julia Lambert.

1522
01:09:04,540 --> 01:09:06,140
Yes, yes, he wrote to me.

1523
01:09:06,140 --> 01:09:08,060
It was my idea. I'm delighted.

1524
01:09:08,060 --> 01:09:09,700
She's very pretty.

1525
01:09:09,700 --> 01:09:11,860
How madly generous of you.

1526
01:09:11,860 --> 01:09:14,260
(Charles) And London was
full of your mischief, Julia.

1527
01:09:14,260 --> 01:09:15,340
(Julia) Was it?

1528
01:09:15,340 --> 01:09:17,820
It sounds as if you
needed a hand to hold.

1529
01:09:17,820 --> 01:09:19,140
Are you through the worst?

1530
01:09:19,140 --> 01:09:20,140
I think my vanity

1531
01:09:20,140 --> 01:09:22,380
was more wounded than my heart.

1532
01:09:22,380 --> 01:09:25,620
I'm so sorry, Julia,
sorry that you've suffered.

1533
01:09:26,060 --> 01:09:29,220
I love you. I always have. Always will.

1534
01:09:31,580 --> 01:09:34,540
Charles, we're miles from home.

1535
01:09:35,300 --> 01:09:38,220
There's no one here who knows us.

1536
01:09:39,540 --> 01:09:41,820
Just... honey...

1537
01:09:41,820 --> 01:09:44,300
What?

1538
01:09:44,300 --> 01:09:47,500
don't let your vanity
be wounded again, um.

1539
01:09:47,820 --> 01:09:50,100
I'm not worth it.

1540
01:09:50,100 --> 01:09:52,780
There'd be no reason.

1541
01:09:52,780 --> 01:09:55,740
I love you
in-- in my own way.

1542
01:09:56,260 --> 01:09:59,420
Julia, we've always
known what that means.

1543
01:09:59,740 --> 01:10:02,940
You can't be in the
theatre and that naive.

1544
01:10:03,700 --> 01:10:06,300
I love you more than you can imagine.

1545
01:10:06,300 --> 01:10:08,260
But...

1546
01:10:08,260 --> 01:10:11,140
But what?

1547
01:10:16,300 --> 01:10:19,180
I play for the other side.

1548
01:10:31,380 --> 01:10:34,420
[Laughing] Charles.

1549
01:10:36,460 --> 01:10:39,340
Oh, darling.

1550
01:10:54,860 --> 01:10:57,740
[Seagulls cawing]

1551
01:11:00,300 --> 01:11:02,860
[Car honking]

1552
01:11:02,860 --> 01:11:05,740
[People chattering]

1553
01:11:06,700 --> 01:11:07,620
Hello.

1554
01:11:07,620 --> 01:11:09,820
(Julia) Oh, Grace.

1555
01:11:09,820 --> 01:11:11,660
I'm so happy you're with us!

1556
01:11:11,660 --> 01:11:15,020
Well, it's not much of a
part, but it is the west end.

1557
01:11:16,380 --> 01:11:17,980
Hello, dear.

1558
01:11:17,980 --> 01:11:20,380
[All chattering]

1559
01:11:20,380 --> 01:11:23,460
Hello, Michael,

1560
01:11:25,700 --> 01:11:28,580
I'd like to introduce
our distinguished author,

1561
01:11:28,580 --> 01:11:29,620
Mr. Walter Gibbs.

1562
01:11:29,620 --> 01:11:30,540
Oh, I can't tell you

1563
01:11:30,540 --> 01:11:33,140
how proud I am that you're on "Nowadays".

1564
01:11:33,140 --> 01:11:33,740
How sweet of you.

1565
01:11:33,740 --> 01:11:37,140
But you've given me a monstrous
speech at the end of the play.

1566
01:11:37,140 --> 01:11:40,020
I hope I can learn it.

1567
01:11:43,740 --> 01:11:45,060
You remember miss Crichton.

1568
01:11:45,060 --> 01:11:47,380
Miss Lambert. Oh, how could I forget.

1569
01:11:47,380 --> 01:11:48,220
She's playing Sybil.

1570
01:11:48,220 --> 01:11:50,660
Miss Lambert, I just
want you to know--

1571
01:11:50,660 --> 01:11:53,540
Have you seen Tom recently?

1572
01:11:54,900 --> 01:11:57,780
Uh, once or twice.

1573
01:11:57,900 --> 01:12:00,900
Miss Lambert, I just want you to know

1574
01:12:01,180 --> 01:12:04,260
I'm going to give my all in this part.

1575
01:12:04,460 --> 01:12:05,980
I'll give it my absolute all.

1576
01:12:05,980 --> 01:12:09,180
Now, now, you mustn't
be a little spendthrift.

1577
01:12:10,300 --> 01:12:12,220
All right, everybody, we'll start.

1578
01:12:12,220 --> 01:12:13,620
(Woman) Yeah.

1579
01:12:13,620 --> 01:12:16,500
So, if you'll find a chair.

